cs.LO, cs.MS, cs.SC, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the formalization of the Laplace transform and its properties using higher-order logic theorem proving. This falls under the category of formal methods and verification, which is covered by cs.LO. The paper also involves the analysis of physical systems, which can be categorized under cs.MS (mathematical physics) or cs.SC (systems and control). The use of Laplace transform in solving differential equations also falls under cs.SY (control theory). Finally, the paper presents an application of the Laplace transform in the analysis of Integrated Circuits (ICs), which can be categorized under cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing).
